    • getMinimumDistance

      public void getMinimumDistance(Node inputNode, Integer edgeCost, Node sourceNode)

      inputNode - The nodes which is currently evaluated.

    • calculateShortestPathFromSource

      public Network calculateShortestPathFromSource(Network network, Node source)
      The method is used to calculate all the pairs source node-final node which has the shortest path between them.
      Parameters:
      network - The given network seen as a graph.
      source - The source node which the algorithm starts first.
      Returns:
      The modified network containing the nodes with the shortest paths between all of them.

    • printPathsAndCosts

      The method is used to print all the paths and costs between the startingNode and all the other nodes in the network.
      Parameters:
      network - The given network (graph).
      startingNode - The starting node used first in the dijkstra algorithm.
